Bug bounty tools
setup environment in the following way.
BugBounty/
├── setup.sh
├── requirements.txt
├── Scripts/
│   ├── syfe_autopwn.sh
│   ├── set_syfe_scope.py
├── tools/
│   └── LinkFinder/
├── Recon/
└── README.md

Place scripts in ~/BugBounty/Scripts/
Create virtual environmnet and then activate it. The command prompt should look something like this: (bountyenv) yourname@host:~/BugBounty/tools$.
cd ~/BugBounty/tools
python3 -m venv bountyenv
source ~/BugBounty/tools/bountyenv/bin/activate

Use the setup.sh and requirements.txt files to install the packages needed for the bug scanner to run.
chmod +x ~/BugBounty/setup.sh
chmod +x ~/BugBounty/requirements.txt
./setup.sh
pip install -r ~/BugBounty/requirements.txt

Use link scanning repo.
git clone https://github.com/GerbenJavado/LinkFinder.git ~/tools/LinkFinder

Install Python requirements for LinkFinder
pip3 install -r ~/tools/LinkFinder/requirements.txt

